Abstract: We present an efficient algorithm for PAC-learning a very general class of geometric concepts over &lt; d for fixed d. More specifically, let T be any set of s halfspaces. Let x = (x 1 ; : : : ; x d ) be an arbitrary point in &lt; d . With each t 2 T we associate a boolean indicator function I t (x) which is 1 if and only if x is in the halfspace t. The concept class, C d s , that we study consists of all concepts formed by any boolean function over I t 1 ; : : : ; I t s for t i 2 T . This class is much more general than any geometric concept class known to be PAC-learnable. Our results can be extended easily to learn efficiently any boolean combination of a polynomial number of concepts selected from any concept class C over &lt; d given that the VC-dimension of C has dependence only on d and there is a polynomial time algorithm to determine if there is a concept from C consistent with a given set of labeled examples. We also present a statistical query version of our algorithm that can tolerate random classification noise. Finally we present a generalization of the standard *-net result of Haussler and Welzl [1987] and apply it to give an alternative noise-tolerant algorithm for d = 2 based on 
